1
00:00:06,874 --> 00:00:08,809
⟨My love for the mysterious person Ai-chan→

2
00:00:08,876 --> 00:00:11,312
Tired of being killed one after another→

3
00:00:11,379 --> 00:00:14,315
Manami locks herself up in a temple and goes on a rampage⟩

4
00:00:14,382 --> 00:00:18,319
⟨Manami reunites with her missing ex-husband Kiryu→

5
00:00:18,386 --> 00:00:21,222
Achieve a revival with Kiryu's words⟩

6
00:00:21,288 --> 00:00:25,226
⟨Just then, Kiryu's car was found in the sea→

7
00:00:25,292 --> 00:00:28,729
There is information that a suicide note was even found...⟩

8
00:00:28,796 --> 00:00:30,731
(Kuroiwa) Manami-san, please calm down!

9
00:00:30,798 --> 00:00:33,234
The body hasn't been brought up yet.

10
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:36,737
(Manami) Huh... Yes.

11
00:00:36,804 --> 00:00:40,307
(Kuroiwa) It looks like the drive recorder was removed.

12
00:00:42,309 --> 00:00:46,814
(Manami) This is an old car with poor fuel efficiency.

13
00:00:48,315 --> 00:00:52,319
(Kiyosumi) The bodies will probably be brought to the surface soon.

14
00:00:55,322 --> 00:00:57,825
Found inside the car.

15
00:01:02,830 --> 00:01:04,765
(Manami) It's the character for Kiryu.

16
00:01:08,769 --> 00:01:15,276
(Manami) ``In my final moments, I decided to die with the car I had been with for many years.''

17
00:01:17,278 --> 00:01:21,215
``The person who called himself Ai-chan and abetted the murder was →

18
00:01:21,282 --> 00:01:24,218
It’s me…”｡

19
00:01:24,285 --> 00:01:26,720
(Kiryu's voice) ``Even though I'm a former police officer→

20
00:01:26,787 --> 00:01:30,224
What threatened the lives of many citizens →

21
00:01:30,291 --> 00:01:36,230
This was a shameful act and I am very sorry.

22
00:01:36,297 --> 00:01:38,732
The motive is →

23
00:01:38,799 --> 00:01:43,737
I wanted to be happy with Manami Tanizaki.

24
00:01:43,804 --> 00:01:46,240
That was it.”

25
00:01:46,307 --> 00:01:53,747
♪～

26
00:01:53,814 --> 00:01:58,752
(Kiryu's voice) "I'm sorry that this happened.

27
00:01:58,819 --> 00:02:03,691
When my love is gone, you'll be with me again... →

28
00:02:03,757 --> 00:02:06,694
I thought something stupid.

29
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:11,699
But I understood.

30
00:02:11,765 --> 00:02:13,701
That day will never come.”

31
00:02:13,767 --> 00:02:18,706
(Kiryu) [Is it okay? I'm happy I don't have to go get it back]

32
00:02:18,772 --> 00:02:24,211
(Kiryu's voice) ``You said something like an understanding ex-husband.

33
00:02:24,278 --> 00:02:27,214
While doing this →

34
00:02:27,281 --> 00:02:30,217
I wanted to feel good at the end.

35
00:02:30,284 --> 00:02:33,220
It's a man's boring pride.

36
00:02:33,287 --> 00:02:37,224
I said, "Even if we break up, we'll still live together" →

37
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:39,793
sorry".

38
00:02:42,296 --> 00:02:45,232
(Kuroiwa) What do you think?

39
00:02:45,299 --> 00:02:47,801
(Manami) Thank you.

40
00:02:49,303 --> 00:02:51,305
>>Yes.

41
00:02:52,806 --> 00:02:56,243
(Manami) This was probably written by Kiryu.

42
00:02:56,310 --> 00:02:59,747
It contains information that only Kiryu and I know.

43
00:02:59,813 --> 00:03:01,749
(Kuroiwa) Well...

44
00:03:01,815 --> 00:03:04,685
>> Ai-chan was Kiryu.

45
00:03:04,752 --> 00:03:09,690
So... I couldn't run away.

46
00:03:09,757 --> 00:03:12,192
That's what it is.

47
00:03:12,259 --> 00:03:16,196
(Manami) When that sacred tree was killed, you were called to the park→

48
00:03:16,263 --> 00:03:18,699
As I said, I was threatened by Ai-chan.

49
00:03:18,766 --> 00:03:22,202
>> You can make as many claims as you like.

50
00:03:22,269 --> 00:03:25,205
It's a made-up story or whatever.

51
00:03:25,272 --> 00:03:29,209
In any case, the investigation headquarters is now disbanded.

52
00:03:29,276 --> 00:03:31,712
(Kuroiwa) Huh? >> No incidents have occurred in 1 month.

53
00:03:31,779 --> 00:03:34,214
That's all that's left.

54
00:03:34,281 --> 00:03:38,786
This is what is called a ``case that I am personally pursuing.''

55
00:03:40,788 --> 00:03:42,723
Thank you for your hard work.

56
00:03:42,790 --> 00:03:51,732
♪～

57
00:03:51,799 --> 00:03:56,237
(Manami) What do you think is the best thing about Kiryu?

58
00:03:56,303 --> 00:03:58,238
(Kuroiwa) Huh?

59
00:03:58,305 --> 00:04:04,178
Huh... What is it? Is it tolerance?

60
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:10,184
(Manami) I think... it's a bit of a sly thing.

61
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:15,689
(Kuroiwa) It's true that he was sneaky this time.

62
00:04:15,756 --> 00:04:19,193
In this form...

63
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:23,197
(Manami) This time→

64
00:04:23,263 --> 00:04:26,200
Rather too honest.

65
00:04:26,266 --> 00:04:28,702
(Kuroiwa) Huh?

66
00:04:28,769 --> 00:04:33,207
(Manami) I would never write out my thoughts honestly in a letter.

67
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:38,212
The type that takes a detour to something more difficult and troublesome.

68
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:43,784
(Kuroiwa) So you think you're alive? Mr. Kiryu.

69
00:04:47,788 --> 00:04:49,723
(Manami) Ah...｡

70
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:52,726
Let's eat at home. (Kuroiwa) At home?

71
00:04:52,793 --> 00:04:56,230
No, this is Chiba. (Manami) My parents' home.

72
00:04:56,296 --> 00:04:59,233
This is Kiryu and I's hometown.

73
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:01,235
(Kuroiwa) My parents' house...!

74
00:05:01,301 --> 00:05:06,173
♪～

75
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:07,675
(Manami) I'm home!

76
00:05:07,741 --> 00:05:09,677
(Kuroiwa) Sorry to bother you... (Kanae) Yes, yes, yes!

77
00:05:09,743 --> 00:05:12,680
(Kanae) Ah, welcome back!

78
00:05:12,746 --> 00:05:14,682
(Manami) My mother Kanae-chan.

79
00:05:14,748 --> 00:05:17,184
Kuroiwa-kun, my colleague detective. (Kuroiwa) Nice to meet you.

80
00:05:17,251 --> 00:05:19,687
I am always indebted to Manami-san.

81
00:05:19,753 --> 00:05:21,689
>> That's my favorite type. (Kuroiwa: Manami) Huh?

82
00:05:21,755 --> 00:05:24,692
When you were a student, didn't you bring in all the kids with faces like this?

83
00:05:24,758 --> 00:05:28,195
(Manami) You know, in this day and age, that kind of thing is sexual harassment.

84
00:05:28,262 --> 00:05:31,198
I don't want to be modest anymore.

85
00:05:31,265 --> 00:05:33,701
>> It's okay.

86
00:05:33,767 --> 00:05:36,704
He looks so happy Ahahaha…｡ (Kuroiwa) Oh no, not really…｡

87
00:05:36,770 --> 00:05:40,774
>> Please take your time. (Kuroiwa) Oh, excuse me... Yes.

88
00:05:42,276 --> 00:05:44,712
>> Hehe! (Manami) What?

89
00:05:44,778 --> 00:05:46,714
(Kuroiwa) What is your type?

90
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:49,783
(Manami) I don't remember. (Kuroiwa) Huh?

91
00:05:51,285 --> 00:05:55,222
>> So Kuroiwa-kun is Manami's love?

92
00:05:55,289 --> 00:05:57,725
(Kuroiwa) Uh... (Manami) That's not true.

93
00:05:57,791 --> 00:06:00,728
You said you wouldn't involve the police. >> Hmm.

94
00:06:00,794 --> 00:06:03,163
(Kuroiwa) What, do you know? About my love.

95
00:06:03,230 --> 00:06:05,666
>> Yeah, it's the three principles of my love.

96
00:06:05,733 --> 00:06:09,169
Don't overdo it, don't get heavy, don't hurt.

97
00:06:09,236 --> 00:06:11,171
(Kuroiwa) I can say it...

98
00:06:11,238 --> 00:06:13,173
(Manami) Because Kanae-chan came up with this. (Kuroiwa) Huh?

99
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:16,176
>> Ahaha! That's right. (Manami) That's right.

100
00:06:16,243 --> 00:06:19,179
>> Even if you play, it won't be fun if you don't set rules, right?

101
00:06:19,246 --> 00:06:22,683
(Kuroiwa) Sigh... It's a free-spirited family.

102
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:26,186
(Manami) Just to be clear, Kanae-chan is devoted to her father.

103
00:06:26,253 --> 00:06:30,758
We work at the city hall and have been good friends ever since we got married at work.

104
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:35,696
(Kuroiwa) ...So when and where did Manami-san meet?

105
00:06:35,763 --> 00:06:39,700
(Manami) Well... it's a mutation!

106
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:41,702
Let's get some rice crackers!

107
00:06:41,769 --> 00:06:45,706
>> I really don't get tired of watching it, hehehe...

108
00:06:45,773 --> 00:06:47,708
Ah, are you going to stay the night today?

109
00:06:47,775 --> 00:06:50,210
(Kuroiwa) Huh? No, no, that's true.

110
00:06:50,277 --> 00:06:53,781
>>Would you like to see Manami's treasured photos?

111
00:07:04,024 --> 00:07:06,460
(Kanae) A photo from a field trip when she was in first grade.

112
00:07:06,527 --> 00:07:09,963
(Kuroiwa) There's a familiar face~ >> It's cute, isn't it?

113
00:07:10,030 --> 00:07:12,966
At this point, my front tooth fell out. (Kuroiwa) Hahaha.

114
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:15,035
Hey~｡

115
00:07:17,538 --> 00:07:20,974
But I see that you are photographed with children of various ages.

116
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:25,479
>> That's right, when I was in 1st grade, I had a female friend from 3rd grade in junior high →

117
00:07:25,546 --> 00:07:28,482
When I was a first year high school student, I played soccer with a fourth grade boy.

118
00:07:28,549 --> 00:07:30,484
(Kuroiwa) Hey.

119
00:07:30,551 --> 00:07:32,986
>> That kid's age doesn't matter.

120
00:07:33,053 --> 00:07:34,988
(Kuroiwa) It's been like that for a long time.

121
00:07:35,055 --> 00:07:37,991
Any special education...? >> No, I haven't. I haven't.

122
00:07:38,058 --> 00:07:42,496
If I had to say it, most people have good points →

123
00:07:42,563 --> 00:07:45,499
Why don't you try looking for it? That's what I said though.

124
00:07:45,566 --> 00:07:48,502
(Kuroiwa) But it's definitely insanely good.

125
00:07:48,569 --> 00:07:51,004
Find the good things about people.

126
00:07:51,071 --> 00:07:55,008
>> I'm really proud of my child.

127
00:07:55,075 --> 00:07:58,011
That's why I can't forgive it.

128
00:07:58,078 --> 00:08:01,081
The guy who's making this child sad.

129
00:08:05,085 --> 00:08:08,021
(Sound of swaying bricks) (Manami) Eh, wait, what are you showing me?

130
00:08:08,088 --> 00:08:10,023
Stop it!

131
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:11,525
(Kuroiwa) Where are you going?

132
00:08:11,592 --> 00:08:13,527
(Manami) Ah, I'm going to have a small class reunion.

133
00:08:13,594 --> 00:08:15,596
(Kuroiwa) Class reunion?

134
00:08:18,599 --> 00:08:23,036
(Nagase) I find it cold that there are police officers I don't know at the reunion.

135
00:08:23,103 --> 00:08:28,041
(Manami) Sorry! He said he really wanted to have a drink with everyone.

136
00:08:28,108 --> 00:08:32,546
(Kuroiwa) Oh, by the way, I met Kiryu-san yesterday...

137
00:08:32,613 --> 00:08:35,983
(Aya) Ah... me. (Kuroiwa) Ah, yes, yes.

138
00:08:36,049 --> 00:08:38,485
Well, Manami-san, let's go. (Manami) Where?

139
00:08:38,552 --> 00:08:40,988
(Kuroiwa) Yes, this way... Everyone, let's have a boys' party later.

140
00:08:41,054 --> 00:08:42,990
(Nagase) Oh, what idiot did you manage...?

141
00:08:43,056 --> 00:08:44,992
(Kuroiwa) Mr. Hongo, Mr. Hongo, too... (Manami) Come here for a moment.

142
00:08:45,058 --> 00:08:46,994
(Kuroiwa) Huh?

143
00:08:47,594 --> 00:08:50,597
(Manami) Wait, what do you mean?

144
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,602
(Kuroiwa) I want them to concentrate on the investigation.

145
00:08:55,669 --> 00:08:57,604
(Manami) I'm sure I'll do it.

146
00:08:57,671 --> 00:09:00,107
There's no such thing as class reunion magic.

147
00:09:00,173 --> 00:09:02,109
(Kuroiwa) Is it true?

148
00:09:02,175 --> 00:09:05,112
"Huh? Something's missing"→

149
00:09:05,178 --> 00:09:08,615
Were there any people who said to you, ``Your sex appeal has come out''?

150
00:09:08,682 --> 00:09:10,684
(Manami) Hmm…｡

151
00:09:12,185 --> 00:09:14,121
(Kuroiwa) Look, it's no good.

152
00:09:14,187 --> 00:09:17,124
(Manami) Just a little~｡

153
00:09:17,190 --> 00:09:21,628
(Kuroiwa) Mr. Nagase, where are you going? The story isn't over yet...

154
00:09:21,695 --> 00:09:23,630
(Manami) Hey, you know... (Aya) Yeah.

155
00:09:23,697 --> 00:09:26,700
(Manami) Where did you meet Kiryu yesterday?

156
00:09:27,701 --> 00:09:30,637
(Aya) We bumped into each other in front of the station.

157
00:09:30,704 --> 00:09:33,140
You don't seem to be feeling very well.

158
00:09:33,206 --> 00:09:36,076
(Aya's voice) "I'm tired of living~" Hahaha→

159
00:09:36,143 --> 00:09:40,147
``It's nice to meet you'' or something like that.

160
00:09:41,648 --> 00:09:44,585
It looked like he was thinking about something.

161
00:09:44,651 --> 00:09:48,088
Eh, you haven't been involved in any incidents, have you?

162
00:09:48,155 --> 00:09:51,091
(Manami) Ah... (Nagase) What, what, are you talking about Kiryu?

163
00:09:51,158 --> 00:09:54,594
What has he been up to lately? (Aya) So yesterday in front of the station...｡

164
00:09:54,661 --> 00:09:57,597
(Kuroiwa) Mr. Nagase! Let's have a drink together over there.

165
00:09:57,664 --> 00:09:59,599
>> Okay, I'll drink here... (Kuroiwa) No, no... here.

166
00:09:59,666 --> 00:10:01,601
>> Why? (Kuroiwa) What will you drink next?

167
00:10:01,668 --> 00:10:03,604
(Nagase) That's enough... (Manami) That guy...｡

168
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:07,607
>> What are you doing just now? (Kuroiwa) Ah... I'm sorry.

169
00:10:07,674 --> 00:10:11,178
I want to talk to you all. >> We have a common topic, right?

170
00:10:12,679 --> 00:10:17,617
(Kuroiwa) You are on the executive committee of Asahi Shopping District's Nebuta Festival.

171
00:10:17,684 --> 00:10:19,619
>> Oh well.

172
00:10:19,686 --> 00:10:23,123
(Kuroiwa) Isn't that mikoshi the best?

173
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:25,625
>> Huh? Do you understand? (Kuroiwa) Of course.

174
00:10:25,692 --> 00:10:28,128
>> It's quite difficult to carry that mikoshi!

175
00:10:28,195 --> 00:10:29,629
(Kuroiwa) That's right.

176
00:10:29,696 --> 00:10:32,132
(Miyata) That mikoshi is the family home that manages it.

177
00:10:32,199 --> 00:10:35,068
Last year, when this guy carried the mikoshi... (Nagase) Are we going to talk about that again?

178
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:40,073
...I was in love with Manami when I was a student.

179
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:42,542
(Miyata) Eh! Well then, please invite me to the after-party with you.

180
00:10:42,609 --> 00:10:44,544
Should I go? (Miyata) You can go.

181
00:10:44,611 --> 00:10:46,546
(Kuroiwa) No, no... >> Huh?

182
00:10:46,613 --> 00:10:48,615
(Kuroiwa) Huh…｡

183
00:10:54,121 --> 00:10:58,625
(Kuroiwa) Huh... I won't let you pass here.

184
00:11:01,128 --> 00:11:03,563
(Manami) Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa.

185
00:11:03,630 --> 00:11:08,068
Now, what should I do with this...

186
00:11:08,135 --> 00:11:12,572
(Kuroiwa) Manami-san... I've done it.

187
00:11:12,639 --> 00:11:14,641
>> Ah, well done...

188
00:11:16,143 --> 00:11:18,078
(Manami) Huh...｡

189
00:11:18,145 --> 00:11:21,081
(Police car siren)

190
00:11:21,148 --> 00:11:26,086
(Iori) Is it okay to say that that incident is over?

191
00:11:26,153 --> 00:11:30,090
(Yuriko) I don't know if Kiryu-kun is dead or not.

192
00:11:30,791 --> 00:11:33,727
Something about that made me feel good.

193
00:11:33,794 --> 00:11:35,062
Huh?

194
00:11:35,128 --> 00:11:39,066
No, it's not good, it's not good...

195
00:11:39,132 --> 00:11:43,637
For some reason, I'm tired and start doubting Manami.

196
00:11:45,739 --> 00:11:48,175
I want to go back.

197
00:11:48,241 --> 00:11:51,778
Manami's strange love story without even thinking about it →

198
00:11:51,845 --> 00:11:54,781
While complaining, I poked the pot.

199
00:11:54,848 --> 00:11:58,852
I guess I can't go back.

200
00:12:02,856 --> 00:12:07,294
There might be someone who attacks Manami-chan next time.

201
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:11,364
That's... that's true though.

202
00:12:14,367 --> 00:12:18,872
That's for Manami to decide.

203
00:12:21,374 --> 00:12:24,811
Yeah... I see.

204
00:12:24,878 --> 00:12:27,814
You're already too overprotective! Because she's not my daughter.

205
00:12:27,881 --> 00:12:30,817
Hehehe sorry, the meddlesome lady showed up again.

206
00:12:30,884 --> 00:12:33,820
It's true, it shows up all the time.

207
00:12:33,887 --> 00:12:36,256
(Iori) I wonder if I can change →

208
00:12:36,323 --> 00:12:38,758
Let's make a decision while having a hotpot. (Yuriko) That's nice.

209
00:12:38,825 --> 00:12:41,261
(Manami) It's heavy! heavy! (Kuroiwa) Ah...ha...

210
00:12:41,328 --> 00:12:43,763
(Manami) Good! (Kuroiwa) Ah! Sigh…｡

211
00:12:43,830 --> 00:12:45,765
(Manami) Ah, I'm tired!

212
00:12:45,832 --> 00:12:50,270
(Kuroiwa) Hey, Kiryu-san is probably still alive.

213
00:12:50,337 --> 00:12:52,772
(Manami) Even if a drunk person says that.

214
00:12:52,839 --> 00:12:57,777
(Kuroiwa) No, seriously! Please wait a moment...

215
00:12:57,844 --> 00:12:59,779
Ugh! (Manami) Hey!

216
00:12:59,846 --> 00:13:02,282
Stop it! (Kuroiwa) Ah...

217
00:13:02,349 --> 00:13:06,787
It seems like Miyata-san also met Kiryu-san yesterday.

218
00:13:06,853 --> 00:13:08,788
(Manami) Huh?

219
00:13:08,855 --> 00:13:11,791
(Miyata) [I also met Kiryu yesterday]

220
00:13:11,858 --> 00:13:13,793
(Kuroiwa) [Huh? ] (Nagase) [Is that so? ]

221
00:13:13,860 --> 00:13:15,795
[He didn't seem to be feeling well]

222
00:13:15,862 --> 00:13:18,298
[“I’m tired of living~” or “I’m glad I met you” →

223
00:13:18,365 --> 00:13:20,801
Don't say anything lonely...]

224
00:13:20,867 --> 00:13:23,303
(Manami's voice) Aya, I'm saying the same thing.

225
00:13:23,370 --> 00:13:27,307
(Kuroiwa) It's a bit too much the same.

226
00:13:27,374 --> 00:13:30,811
(Manami) I purposely met with you to secure a witness.

227
00:13:30,877 --> 00:13:33,813
(Kuroiwa) Yes, it is.

228
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:36,249
(Manami) I see.

229
00:13:36,316 --> 00:13:39,252
(Kuroiwa) Hey, I'm glad I followed you, right?

230
00:13:39,319 --> 00:13:41,755
(Manami) Huh? Even just one person could listen to it.

231
00:13:41,821 --> 00:13:44,758
(Kuroiwa) Oh, that's terrible! Hehehe.

232
00:13:44,825 --> 00:13:47,761
(Manami) But thank you!

233
00:13:47,827 --> 00:13:50,830
You're a kind detective.

234
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,769
(Kuroiwa) That's sneaky.

235
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:57,771
(Manami) What?

236
00:13:57,837 --> 00:14:00,774
(Kuroiwa) You know, it's really not good for you.

237
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:04,277
(Manami) Wow. Are you the type who preaches when you get drunk?

238
00:14:04,344 --> 00:14:06,279
I'm not good at it.

239
00:14:06,346 --> 00:14:08,281
(Kuroiwa) I know that's about it.

240
00:14:08,348 --> 00:14:10,283
Absolutely not.

241
00:14:10,350 --> 00:14:12,285
I've never even had sashimeshi before.

242
00:14:12,352 --> 00:14:14,788
(Manami) Huh? Is that so?

243
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:17,791
Didn't you eat ramen or something?

244
00:14:17,857 --> 00:14:20,293
At my desk. (Kuroiwa) Last January, right?

245
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:22,295
That's a no-go.

246
00:14:22,362 --> 00:14:24,798
Shiretto Kiyosumi-san was there.

247
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:27,801
(Manami) I remember it well... haha.

248
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:30,804
(Kuroiwa) There are people who say that it will never happen →

249
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:34,241
It's probably easier to hate it.

250
00:14:34,307 --> 00:14:36,243
(Manami) That's right~｡

251
00:14:36,309 --> 00:14:39,312
Because I can't be happy.

252
00:14:40,814 --> 00:14:43,316
(Kuroiwa) It's okay to be unhappy.

253
00:14:45,819 --> 00:14:50,257
(Kiryu) [We'll decide that part]

254
00:14:50,323 --> 00:14:53,326
[Include whether you want to be happy]

255
00:15:03,336 --> 00:15:05,772
(Kuroiwa) Manami-san.

256
00:15:05,839 --> 00:15:07,340
(Manami) Hmm…｡

257
00:15:11,845 --> 00:15:13,847
(Kuroiwa) I love it.

258
00:15:19,853 --> 00:15:22,289
(Kuroiwa) I don't think there are many.

259
00:15:22,355 --> 00:15:26,860
Someone who cares about Manami as much as I do.

260
00:15:30,363 --> 00:15:34,234
(Kamiki) [Ai-chan is a person who cares about you]

261
00:15:34,301 --> 00:15:38,805
(Kuroiwa) [No, you're not the culprit]

262
00:15:40,307 --> 00:15:43,243
>> [It's really important]

263
00:15:43,310 --> 00:15:45,812
[by Manami]

264
00:15:49,816 --> 00:15:51,818
(Manami) Sorry...｡

265
00:15:57,824 --> 00:16:02,262
(sleeping)

266
00:16:02,329 --> 00:16:04,831
(Manami) Huh...｡

267
00:16:09,336 --> 00:16:11,338
(sound of door opening)

268
00:16:12,839 --> 00:16:15,275
drink? (Manami) Yes.

269
00:16:15,342 --> 00:16:19,279
I didn't expect him to be such a troublesome person to get drunk.

270
00:16:19,346 --> 00:16:25,352
>> Hehe... Kuroiwa-kun, are you okay? (Manami) It's okay, it's okay.

271
00:16:29,356 --> 00:16:32,359
(Manami) Huh…｡ >> Manami｡

272
00:16:39,299 --> 00:16:41,801
Manami.

273
00:16:45,805 --> 00:16:49,242
(Manami) No way.

274
00:16:49,309 --> 00:16:52,812
Not at all.

275
00:16:59,319 --> 00:17:04,324
(Manami) Maybe, I think I'm scared.

276
00:17:06,826 --> 00:17:13,767
(Manami's voice) The people I love are dying one after another.

277
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:18,772
Some people thought it might be okay to believe →

278
00:17:18,838 --> 00:17:24,277
The person I believed in for so long is gone.

279
00:17:24,344 --> 00:17:27,781
Even the people who care about me →

280
00:17:27,847 --> 00:17:30,350
I can't believe it.

281
00:17:32,352 --> 00:17:36,790
If this continues, there will be no one left →

282
00:17:36,856 --> 00:17:39,359
It's scary.

283
00:17:41,361 --> 00:17:44,297
>> I'm here though.

284
00:17:44,364 --> 00:17:49,302
I'm going to die soon, so no excuses? (Manami) Haha.

285
00:17:49,369 --> 00:17:52,872
I'm not that bad of a guy though.

286
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:59,813
>> That's how you cry when you're scared.

287
00:17:59,879 --> 00:18:04,317
Don't force yourself to laugh.

288
00:18:04,384 --> 00:18:06,319
(Manami) Yes.

289
00:18:06,386 --> 00:18:19,399
♪～

290
00:18:24,671 --> 00:18:27,106
(Kuroiwa) Ha...

291
00:18:27,173 --> 00:18:32,178
Ugh… it hurt when it was warm…｡

292
00:18:33,279 --> 00:18:35,215
Umm... >> Good morning.

293
00:18:35,281 --> 00:18:37,717
(Kuroiwa) Good morning. >> Are you okay with your hangover?

294
00:18:37,784 --> 00:18:39,486
(Kuroiwa) No... >> Do you want to drink miso soup?

295
00:18:39,552 --> 00:18:42,989
(Kuroiwa) Ah... Thank you...

296
00:18:43,056 --> 00:18:44,991
(Manami) I'm home. >> Welcome back!

297
00:18:45,058 --> 00:18:46,993
(Kuroiwa) Eh, are you going home in the morning?

298
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:49,996
(Manami) Hmm, yeah.

299
00:18:50,063 --> 00:18:52,499
Wow! It's delicious.

300
00:18:52,565 --> 00:18:54,934
(Kuroiwa) But the man went home yesterday.

301
00:18:55,001 --> 00:18:58,438
(Manami) Yes, that's why it's with Aya.

302
00:18:58,505 --> 00:19:02,942
(Kuroiwa) Ah, karaoke? You're doing well.

303
00:19:03,009 --> 00:19:05,512
(Manami) No... (Kuroiwa) Eh.

304
00:19:08,515 --> 00:19:13,453
(Kuroiwa) Wow, that's right...

305
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:17,457
I arbitrarily separated it into men and women.

306
00:19:17,524 --> 00:19:21,961
(Manami) “Alumni Magic Frame” has been born!

307
00:19:22,028 --> 00:19:24,531
Pururu... Yaho!

308
00:19:26,032 --> 00:19:28,968
>> Not yet.

309
00:19:29,035 --> 00:19:31,037
Hmm.

310
00:19:33,039 --> 00:19:35,475
(Kuroiwa) Itadakimasu.

311
00:19:35,542 --> 00:19:38,978
Sorry to bother you at your parents' house.

312
00:19:39,045 --> 00:19:42,982
(Manami) Huh? I really enjoyed it.

313
00:19:43,049 --> 00:19:45,985
I really got along with Kanae-chan.

314
00:19:46,052 --> 00:19:48,488
(Kuroiwa) Well, we have the same recommendation.

315
00:19:48,555 --> 00:19:50,990
(Manami) Huh? Who do you recommend?

316
00:19:51,057 --> 00:19:55,428
(Kuroiwa) Don't tell. (Manami) What is that?

317
00:19:55,495 --> 00:19:58,998
(Kuroiwa) Um... Now that I think about it, I was last night...

318
00:20:01,501 --> 00:20:03,937
(Manami) Yeah...｡

319
00:20:04,003 --> 00:20:07,307
(Kuroiwa) My memory of last night is a little vague. (Manami) Oh, that's right.

320
00:20:07,373 --> 00:20:10,310
(Kuroiwa) Was there something wrong with you? (Manami) Ah, no, not at all!

321
00:20:10,376 --> 00:20:12,312
It was a little noisy.

322
00:20:12,378 --> 00:20:14,380
(Kuroiwa) Ah... I'm sorry.

323
00:20:18,384 --> 00:20:20,887
(Manami) Not at all...｡

324
00:20:24,390 --> 00:20:30,830
📱(vibration sound)

325
00:20:30,897 --> 00:20:32,832
(Kuroiwa) Huh? 📱(vibration sound)

326
00:20:32,899 --> 00:20:35,835
📱(vibration sound)

327
00:20:35,902 --> 00:20:39,339
(Kimyo) These are all the documents that were on Mr. Kamiki's desk.

328
00:20:39,405 --> 00:20:43,343
(Manami) Thank you for your cooperation. >> No…｡

329
00:20:43,409 --> 00:20:48,348
But Mr. Kamiki, what were you hiding so much?

330
00:20:48,414 --> 00:20:55,788
♪～

331
00:20:55,855 --> 00:20:57,790
(Manami) Huh...｡

332
00:20:57,857 --> 00:21:13,306
♪～

333
00:21:13,373 --> 00:21:18,811
📱(vibration sound)

334
00:21:18,878 --> 00:21:20,813
(Manami) What happened?

335
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:23,316
📱 I'm about to meet Kiryu-san.

336
00:21:23,383 --> 00:21:26,319
Kiryu? What do you mean?

337
00:21:26,386 --> 00:21:30,323
📱 He was alive after all (Kuroiwa) Just as Manami said.

338
00:21:30,390 --> 00:21:33,393
(Manami) Wait, I'll go too.

339
00:21:35,395 --> 00:21:38,331
(Kuroiwa's voice) Are we finally going to move forward?

340
00:21:38,398 --> 00:21:42,335
(Manami's voice) Yeah, maybe... I'll move on.

341
00:21:42,402 --> 00:21:44,837
(Kuroiwa's voice) Manami-san this→

342
00:21:44,904 --> 00:21:47,340
It might not be the right thing to say now, but →

343
00:21:47,407 --> 00:21:51,344
I wanted to get fired up because it was a game.

344
00:21:51,411 --> 00:21:53,279
May I?

345
00:21:53,346 --> 00:21:55,281
(Manami's voice) Yeah...｡

346
00:21:55,348 --> 00:22:01,788
(Kuroiwa's voice) Once you've calmed down, would you like to have dinner together?

347
00:22:01,854 --> 00:22:06,292
(Manami's voice) Yeah... let's go.

348
00:22:06,359 --> 00:22:14,801
♪～

349
00:22:14,867 --> 00:22:18,304
(Manami) Kuroiwa-kun! Kuroiwa-kun!

350
00:22:18,371 --> 00:22:20,373
Huh...

351
00:22:22,875 --> 00:22:27,814
Huh… hah…｡

352
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:30,316
(Iori) What are you doing?

353
00:22:30,383 --> 00:22:41,327
♪～

354
00:22:41,394 --> 00:22:44,831
(Iori) First of all, how do you explain this situation?

355
00:22:44,897 --> 00:22:47,333
(Manami) Oh, that's wrong! this is….

356
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:49,836
>> It's only natural.

357
00:22:49,902 --> 00:22:53,773
♪～

358
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:55,775
(Manami) Ah...｡

359
00:22:55,842 --> 00:23:02,348
♪～
